// Adversarial: SpeedBoost(1.05) fires on Impact(Breaker) — every bolt-breaker contact
// applies a small multiplicative speed increase. Corridor layout is chosen because it
// maximises wall bounces and breaker contacts: the narrow channel funnels the bolt back
// to the breaker repeatedly at high frequency. chaos 0.3 keeps the breaker moving but
// not erratically, so the bolt reliably returns to the breaker rather than draining.
// The adversarial risk: if Impact(Breaker) fires on both BoltImpactBreaker AND a
// secondary event (e.g., BreakerImpactCell when the breaker body passes a cell),
// SpeedBoost fires twice per breaker contact. In a Corridor layout with 8000 frames at
// ~64 Hz the bolt may contact the breaker hundreds of times: 1.05^200 ≈ 1.7 billion.
// A secondary risk: if the bridge system iterates all entities with BoundEffects and
// the bolt entity is processed multiple times in the same frame (duplicate query result),
// the same boost fires N times per tick. BoltSpeedAccurate fires the moment speed leaves
// the configured envelope. NoNaN detects velocity overflow to infinity. BoltInBounds
// catches the bolt escaping bounds after extreme velocity magnitudes.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Corridor",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.3)),
    max_frames: 4000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltInBounds, BoltSpeedAccurate, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 5003,
    initial_effects: [
        Stamp(ActiveBolts, When(Impact(Breaker), Fire(SpeedBoost((multiplier: 1.05))))),
    ],
)
